						               													<description>In the Settlers of Catan &amp;quot;Einsteiger-Variante&amp;quot; (First-time user), the award-winning game is reduced in size (with an edge-lenght of 25 mm) and with printed numbers on the hex pieces to allow for quick play and introduction to casual players. The Settlers of Catan are once again traveling through the lands of Catan, racing to develop their settlements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players are now able to gain the flavour of the popular board game within 75 minutes with simplified board that allows quick game setup and learning. The Catan board game continues to have a modular board and the variety of strategic options available that made the original Settlers of Catan game so popular.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is an exclusive edition for the German discounter &amp;quot;Penny&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules are the same as for CATAN.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Belongs to the Catan Series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Re-implements:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    CATAN&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     3 double-sided large island patches with 4 hex and 3 harbors each&amp;#10;     3 small cardboard pieces to be put between the island patches&amp;#10;     6 interlocking pieces to be put between island patch and small cardboard  piece&amp;#10;     7 double-sided single hex pieces&amp;#10;     20 cardboard settlement pieces&amp;#10;     16 cardboard city pieces&amp;#10;     60 cardboard road pieces&amp;#10;     95 resource cards&amp;#10;     25 development cards&amp;#10;     4 cardboard tables overview of building costs&amp;#10;     2 special bonus cards&amp;#10;     2 six-sided wooden dice&amp;#10;     1 Robber piece consists of 2 cardboard pieces&amp;#10;     20 Trading chips for the 2 player variant&amp;#10;     1 Games Rules &amp;amp; Almanac Booklet&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
